    <span class="author" data-post-author="nibb"><a href="http://arstechnica.com/civis/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=330040&amp;sid=e8d81635141051048bc0dd167efd8d9f">nibb</a></span><span class="rank">Ars Tribunus Militum</span>
      <aside class="icons">
        
        <a href="http://arstechnica.com/business/2013/09/pioneering-bitcoin-hardware-company-to-offer-full-refunds-for-all-chip-orders/?comments=1&post=25256289#comment-25256289" title="2013-09-09T19:19:17-05:00" class="timeago datetime">Mon Sep 09, 2013 6:19 pm</a>
        
        <span class="hidden-icon-start"></span>
        
      </aside>
    </header>
    <div class="body">
      Maybe those scammers from butterfly labs should do the same. They accept pre orders, this means money without refund options and they ship nothing. Some of their customers are waiting for over a year. They did not even ship 1% of the orders they received.<br /><br />I feel sorry for people that ordered this year. A company should &quot;NOT&quot; accept money from a customer until it already shipped the product. Amazon and every other store in the US accepts pre orders but only charge once they product is shipped, this means not only do they have what you paid, but its on its way.<br /><br />How is this even legal is something I will never understand. You charge people money, imagine thousands and thousands of US$ and ship nothing. Not only are you using customers money to finance your business which is already wrong but people are short on money. This seems like a nice scam, collect a couple of millions, put them them in the bank, collects interests then refund.<br /><br />Butterfly labs not only says they ship products in 2 months on their website which is a complete lie, but they say orders are final no refunds. Really? You pay something and if its not there in 2 months like they say, you can´t request money back. They are surely doing something illegal because they don´t even promise 2 months, they say average of 2 months so this can mean never.<br /><br />Someone should intervene these companies and force them to refund people that still never received anything. If they want to sell something, then they should ship something. They charge and deliver nothing. They only send a few devices to the media, Ars included to increase their sales, it was pure marketing and they also shipped like a dozens of units to people that pay last year, but seems nothing but a huge pyramid scheme, they will eventually blow up and allot of people will be without money and product left.<br /><br />Butterfly labs is such a huge scam, that instead of shipping units they keep offering customers new options so they can increase their wait time. Now that they had to have shipped most of their units by this time of this year, their customers received again a promotion to upgrade and pay a bit more for new units. So they can take more money and have a bit more time before the things blow up in their face.
      
    </div>
