      From my understanding of mining of Bitcoin is that it's like finding Prime Numbers. The more that are found, the harder it is to find more. There is one difference if what I read is correct. While there is no end to Prime Numbers, there is a fixed number of Bitcoins. Once they are all found, there aren't any more.<br /><br />I can't verify what I just said, because I can't find the bookmark from where I read it. But if true, it does put a different light on things.
      
