lict whatsoever.</div><br /><br />You probably paid by PayPal. They only accept PayPal for singles ones for a reason, because it seems they don´t want to mess up with their PayPal account, so it could be that they actually are refunding orders made via PayPal to avoid disputes. But they do not accept PayPal for bigger orders. How come? Does that sound strange? Because they don´t refund them.<br /><br />Also someone already commented on this, with all the money they make, they can actually refund only with interests made from that money. If they had thousands of people paying them 300$, because their singles have like a 30$ plus shipping fee on top of their prices which makes it a bit more than 300$ and someone requests a refund 3 months later, they made some money out of it. Now they have so many of this orders they can probably do refunds for a couple of them. But good luck if you paid with bitcoins or any other method.<br /><br />Also, they publish in their own website that orders are final and they only approve refunds manually on a case per case basis. What does that tell you? They can say yes to some refunds and no to others.<br /><br />If they are have no problems with refunds, what do they not say it so? I don´t think this is the case, I think most people are never going to get their money back if they request a refund.
      
